cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal logic and unsatisfiable cores. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses conflict-driven solvers, which are commonly used in AI. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the problem of inconsistent compliance rules in contract-based or service-based systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses declarative design and evolution of rules. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses automated support for early declarative design.
